===Etymology 4===
{{zh-forms|s=侪|alt=纔,裁,全,惢}}

Likely a development from {{zh-l|全|tr=-}}. The use of the glyph {{zh-l|儕}} was first attested in writing in the Ming Dynasty, in ''The Mountain Songs'' ({{lang|zh|山歌}}) by {{w|Feng Menglong}} as a sound-borrowing.

Alternatively, {{zh-ref|Shen (2017)}} posits that this sense might be a grammaticalisation of Etymology 1.

